{"id": 225008348, "title": "Nurse made me check baby's name three times - she thought I made spelling mistake", "text": "When it comes to naming a baby, most parents spend hours mulling over their options before deciding on a moniker. But one mum has been left scratching her head over a possible spelling mistake she made when naming her second-born son. She explained how every time the nurse came to check on her after giving birth, she asked her whether she was sure about the spelling of her son's name, making her question it again and again. She said on Reddit: \"My husband and I agreed on the name Gregory. Each time a new nurse came in to check on me and our baby, they asked what his name was. \"I would answer \"Gregory\". I think 4 nurses either asked me to spell that or wanted me to confirm how it was spelled. I was so puzzled because I didn't know there was more than one way to spell Gregory. I wondered if I had made a mistake and misspelled his name.\" Read more: Sign up to Mirror US's SMS updates for the latest straight from the newsroom For all the latest on news, politics, sports, and showbiz from the USA, go to The Mirror US. Confused, she shared how she had a \"very long labour\" and is now second guessing how she spelt her child's name. She added: \"I wonder if they kept asking in case we had cooked up some crazy spelling for Gregory. So, for fun, turn Gregory into a tragedy. I think you could easily add a y and make it Greygory.\" In response, one user said: \"Greigor\u2019eigh.\" Another user added: \"Ghraegourieye\" A third user said: That spelling reads like someone trying to win at Scrabble.\" One more user said: \"A lot of hospitals do this just to every newborn to make sure that their sleep-deprived parents didn't make a spelling mistake.\" Do you have a story to share? Email paige.freshwater@reachplc.com.", "summary": "A woman has been left scratching her head after being asked to check the spelling of her newborn son's name three times in the hospital to make sure she wasn't making a spelling mistake", "url": "https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/us-news/nurse-made-check-babys-name-32915093", "image": "https://i2-prod.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article32876586.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_Cute-Baby-Feet-In-Beige-Socks-Child-With-Mother-On-Bed-Happy-Motherhood.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 12:27:08", "author": "Paige Freshwater,Paige-freshwater", "authors": ["Paige Freshwater", "Paige-freshwater"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.587}